reviewText: The best comedic dvd out there! Mr. Slocumb's delivery of CFC (cuss free comedy) let's one know you can still be extremely funny and entertaining without the use of profanity.  A dvd truly for the entire family. A MUST buy! You will find yourself watching it over and over again and sharing it with everyone.  I enjoyed it so much that after making my initial purchase, I purchased three (3) additional copies for gifts.  Trust me, this will become your most favorite comedic dvd!

This is a great, clean family comedy show that will have you rolling on the floor most of the time. If you grew up in the African American church and like good Christian jokes, this is the DVD for you. Great to show to Christian groups.

Given 3 stars, this is two seperate concerts merged into one. The classic Kool & the Gang (b/4 JT), mostly funky, jazzy inspired soul music, the original band is jamming. On the tracks with JT as lead vocalist, there are a few different lead singers sitting in for JT! They sound pretty good, but you can see that there are different stages, band members, and sounds. If you like Kool & the Gang, this dvd is average. The music from the band is Kool & the Gang, but with each song going back & forth between two different concerts, it can be unsettling! Is there a concert with JT performing with the group?

Jonathan a very funny guy and I enjoy his dvd's. This one is good,has some funny moments, however I really liked laugh yourself to life over this one. I still will say that this one is ok to get too. It came well packaged and quick arrival and was a good purchase.

This was refreshing to watch/  I showed this video on a bus trip and several people expressed an interest in buying it.

Not quite as good at Laugh Yourself To Life, but much better than most of the stuff out there today. Jonathan is totally professional and yet able to bring the audience in to his world. A warm comedian who is able to take on church folk and keep them laughing (not an  easy job). I love the fact that he gave props to Rev Jeremiah Wright. That takes heart in the mamby pamby society. I am and will be a fan. Go Jonathan.
Hilarious for the most part.  I did not care for the profanity used in quoting Rev. Jeremiah Wright during the first part of the comedy act.  Christian comedy should be void of profanity.
